transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: This is Tom Stevenson calling.

Speaker 1: I want to cancel my account. This is the second time I've tried to do this.

Speaker 2: Okay, you called prior or you sent an email?

Speaker 1: I called back right after Christmas.

Speaker 2: Really?

Speaker 1: And I got a hold of the Go-Go Meds or whoever the hell it was.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: They said they would relay it to you, which they did not, obviously.

Speaker 2: Because I just got another prescription in the mail.

Speaker 1: For $63.95, which I cannot use unless I want to die.

Speaker 2: Oh yeah, no, no, no.

Speaker 1: We don't want that, Mr. Stevenson.

Speaker 2: But what happened? Because you provided us the medical survey.

Speaker 1: And we approved you based on that.

Speaker 2: If you had such a severe medical condition,

Speaker 1: we would have canceled your order right away since the beginning.

Speaker 2: But you provided us with information.

Speaker 1: That's why we wrote the prescription for you.

Speaker 2: I understand that.

Speaker 1: But you know, it's something in that stuff that doesn't agree with me.

Speaker 2: I get severe headaches.

Speaker 1: I get dizzy and my heart just jumps and my blood pressure skyrocketed.

Speaker 2: I called my regular doctor and he said do not take those under any circumstances.

Speaker 1: I agree, I agree.

Speaker 2: But at least we had to try to find out, right?

Speaker 1: No, I agree.

Speaker 2: When you report us, we got to stop.

Speaker 1: And that was your first time taking Viagra, right?

Speaker 2: I'm just asking a question for documentation purposes.

Speaker 1: That was your first time?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it was my first time taking this stuff.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then did you take Cialis in the past?

Speaker 2: Because those are the two...

Speaker 1: No, I have not.

Speaker 2: I took Viagra and that didn't set too well with me.

Speaker 1: And my doctor said that I should try this Cialis or whatever it is.

Speaker 2: And obviously that didn't work for me either.

Speaker 1: So I need to cancel this prescription.

Speaker 2: I don't want to get any more.

Speaker 1: And, you know, I've got nine pills in here now that I can't use.

Speaker 2: Cost me $63.95.

Speaker 1: I'm not happy about that either.

Speaker 2: No, I understand, Mr. Stevenson.

Speaker 1: I'm going to help you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I was asking for Cialis because obviously we try to find solutions here.

Speaker 1: We like to hear good testimony.

Speaker 2: I was trying to get you maybe a sample of Cialis even though we canceled the Viagra.

Speaker 1: And you could call and be like, hey, Cialis worked or Cialis didn't work.

Speaker 2: So we could at least give it a try because they're completely different medicine.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, it doesn't work.

Speaker 2: I don't want to try any more.

Speaker 1: You know, I'm 78 years old and I'd like to live a little bit longer.

Speaker 2: But if I keep taking that stuff, I won't.

Speaker 1: So, anyway, you want the NRX number?

Speaker 2: No, I got you.

Speaker 1: I see you here.

Speaker 2: I'm going to cancel for you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, everything will be canceled.

Speaker 1: Nothing to worry about, Tom, Mr. Stevenson.

Speaker 2: If you can take it, you can take it.

Speaker 1: You know what I mean?

Speaker 2: That's right.

Speaker 1: I mean, you know, it's not your fault, but I can't take it.

Speaker 2: I can't take it.

Speaker 1: But what bothers me is I called the first time to Go-Go Meds or whoever it was.

Speaker 2: They said they were going to take care of it.

Speaker 1: And then I get another prescription.

Speaker 2: I'm going, you know, I can't afford $63.95 and just throw this away.

Speaker 1: So...

Speaker 2: No, I understand that.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I cancel everything for you.

Speaker 2: And yeah, you all said so.

Speaker 1: I cancel everything, okay?

Speaker 2: Prescription, account.

Speaker 1: And please note that, you know, you can't take it due to a side effect, okay?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So you all said and thank you for making time to call.

Speaker 2: And yeah, I apologize for any confusion and everything. I've been taking care of it for you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, very good.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You have a good day.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a great week.

Speaker 2: Yeah, bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
